description: #cricketlive #cricketmatch #indvsseng INDIA vs ENGLAND, 5th Test Final Day Live Commentary | IND vs ENG, Test Live Match Today | Last InngINDIA VS ENGALND Test 5 Day 4 Preview :England need 324 more runs to win the match and the series, while India are effectively eight wickets away from leveling the series 2-2 (assuming Woakes won‚Äôt come out to bat).With England 233/6, needing 35 more to win, and India just four wickets away from a series-levelling triumph, bad light and rain brought an early end to a gripping day. Chris Woakes was seen padded up in his whites yesterday, hinting he could bat today if needed despite the shoulder injury.The final day promises high drama‚Äîwill India snatch victory, can England hold their nerve, or will we witness a once-in-a-generation tie? Don‚Äôt blink. Every ball today could decide the series!Early stumps on Day 4 due to a wet outfield. England need just 35 runs; India need 4 wickets (assuming Chris Woakes comes out to bat). Boos ring around the ground, but like the previous four matches in this series, the final Test will also head into a fifth day. The day started well for the visitors as they knocked over Ben Dukett and Ollie Pope in quick succession to push the hosts on the back foot. England were 106 for three at one stage and needed 268 runs to win. Joe Root and Harry Brook then played out of their skins and put on a stunning partnership of 195 runs for the fourth wicket.Brook was on 19 when he gave India an opportunity but Mohammed Siraj, at deep backward square leg, took the catch and stepped on the boundary cushions. That triggered something in Brook and he unleashed his fury on the Indian bowlers.In a bid to get quick runs, Brook miscued one to Siraj, who managed to hold onto it and ended his knock at 111. Root was steady as he brought up his 39th Test hundred. However, trying to steer one to third man, he edged the ball straight to the keeper. description: Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine‚Äôs daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, K√≠la Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.
